title: Cohort Definition for Cervical Cancer Screening Measure
description: The percentage of women 21–64 years of age who were screened for cervical cancer using either of the following criteria: 1. Women 21–64 years of age who had cervical cytology performed every 3 years; 2. Women 30–64 years of age who had cervical cytology/human papillomavirus (HPV) co-testing performed every 5 years.
